.SH "NAME"
pci_enable_rom \- enable ROM decoding for a PCI device
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ pci_enable_rom('u
.BI "int pci_enable_rom(struct\ pci_dev\ *\ " "pdev" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIpdev\fR
.RS 4
PCI device to enable
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Enable ROM decoding on
\fIdev\fR\&. This involves simply turning on the last bit of the PCI ROM BAR\&. Note that some cards may share address decoders between the ROM and other resources, so enabling it may disable access to MMIO registers or other card memory\&.
